FBIS4-36888 "drnes114dd_94001" FBIS-NES-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 Palestinian Affairs Shadow Government Reportedly Formed in Jerusalem Shadow Government Reportedly Formed in Jerusalem TA1306151894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 13 Jun 94 TA1306151894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Faysal al-Husayni is establishing a shadow government in East Jerusalem to be made up of nine ministries. A Palestinian source told our correspondent Moti Amir that the shadow government will be headed by a prime minister, two deputy prime ministers, and a financial inspector general who will deal with the expenses of the government and coordinate it with the expenditures of the Palestinian Authority in the self-rule areas. The shadow government will also include a political affairs ministry and a defense and general security ministry, contrary to the Palestinian Authority in the self-rule areas.
